note.p:
Pub. L. 115–427, § 7(a), Jan. 9, 2019, 132 Stat. 5507, provided that:
“(a) In General.—Not less than annually, the Secretary of State shall provide, to the foreign minister of each country that has been downgraded to a ‘Tier 2 Watch List’ country pursuant to the Trafficking in Persons report submitted under section 110(b) of the Trafficking Victims Protection Act of 2000 (22 U.S.C. 7107(b))—“(1) a copy of the annual Trafficking in Persons report; and

“(2) information pertinent to that country’s downgrade, including—“(A) confirmation of the country’s designation to the Tier 2 Watch List;

“(B) the implications associated with such designation and the consequences for the country of a downgrade to Tier 3;

“(C) the factors that contributed to the downgrade; and

“(D) the steps that the country must take to be considered for an upgrade in status of designation.”
